liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Keanu Vincente who is in northern Israel says he and other Australians needs the government to "step up and take our people home". "I feel a bit stranded, especially when I see other repatriation flights coming from other countries," he told ABC's News Breakfast. "It would feel a lot safer and more guarenteed to have the Australian government doing those flights for all the Australians here." Yesterday, Foreign Minister Penny Wong said "all options' were being considered to help Australians leave Israel. There are more than 10,000 Australians living in Israel, and more who are visiting as tourists. The official advice to Australians looking to leave is to take up commercial flights, however there have been widespread cancellations. Shadow Foreign Minsiter Simon Birmingham says repatriation flights should be looked at. "Repatriation flights for Australians out of Israel are one option that should be actively considered," he said. "Ultimately its for the government to find the best, fastest and safest way to help Australians to get home."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Australian in Israel calls on government to step up efforts to bring people home

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: ABC correspondent Nick Dole has been in southern Israel — the hotspot in this war so far. Roads are gradually reopening near the Gaza border as Israeli troops clear the area of Hamas militants. As you drive, you're presented with grim reminders of what happened here. We found this badly damaged car about 10 kilometres from the Gaza border. Whoever was inside was heading towards Gaza when their vehicle came under attack. The windows are smashed, the wheels are blown-out and the exterior is riddled with holes. Shrapnel has spread throughout the car. On the ground is a backpack. It's had its straps cut with something sharp like scissors or a knife. In the boot are several pairs of shoes and a coffee pot. It appears to be a rental. Whoever was in the car would be lucky to survive the attack. But then, they may have had to endure an even more terrifying ordeal at the hands of Hamas militants.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: A stark reminder of violence in Israel's south
